location: 2132 Kingsbury Cir, Santa Clara, CA
description: On February 5, 2025 in Santa Clara, an autonomous minivan traveling about 16 mph along Kingsbury Circle made a right turn and, after the safety driver took over because of an inaccurate map causing the vehicle to run close to parked cars, its right blind-spot sensor pod struck the left rear-view mirror of a parked Honda Accord; both vehicles sustained minor damage and the Level 4 ADS was not engaged at impact.

location: Bryant Street and 16th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox autonomous SUV stopped at a red light on northbound Bryant Street at 16th Street in San Francisco was rear‑ended by a passenger car that had been stopped behind it and then inched forward while the Zoox vehicle remained stationary; the Zoox operator disengaged after impact, the Zoox vehicle’s rear bumper had minor damage, police were not called, and a later notice reported an unspecified injury allegation from the Zoox operator.

location: 3113 Pine St, Martinez, CA
description: While traveling northbound at about 20 mph on Pine Street in Martinez, a May Mobility autonomous shuttle was struck on the passenger side by a black Subaru Forester that drove straight out of a driveway into the roadway without slowing or stopping; the May operator tried to swerve left but could not avoid the broadside collision.

manufacturer: MERCEDES-BENZ RESEARCH & DEVELOPMENT NORTH AMERICA, INC.
location: BACK PARKING LOT OF NVIDIA ENDEAVOR, SANTA CLARA, CA
description: In the back parking lot of Nvidia’s Endeavor office in Santa Clara, a Mercedes-Benz test vehicle driven in conventional mode stopped and was shifted into Park next to other parked cars and perpendicular to a Chevrolet Camaro; while the Mercedes-Benz remained stationary, the Camaro reversed out of its space and struck the Mercedes-Benz at the right rear door, causing minor damage to both vehicles and no reported injuries, and the incident was reported under OL 316 as a precaution.

location: 2034 Main Street, Mountain View, CA
description: On June 10, 2025, a Nuro autonomous vehicle driving near a curbside trash can that was positioned some distance from the curb brushed the can with its side mirror; the can stayed in place and the vehicle only received negligible damage to a plastic side-mirror attachment.

location: Westbound 16th Street between Potrero and Bryant, San Francisco, CA
description: Around 6 p.m. on September 2, 2025, a Nuro Prius being driven manually westbound in the left lane of 16th Street just past Potrero Avenue in San Francisco struck a vehicle that emerged from a driveway on the right and tried to cross both westbound lanes to enter an eastbound lane through gaps in traffic; the Nuro vehicle could not stop completely before contact, and both vehicles sustained minor damage with no injuries reported.

location: Linda Vista Ave. and Terra Bella Ave, Mountain View, CA
description: On July 30, 2025, a Nuro Prius in autonomous mode stopped at a sign-controlled intersection at Linda Vista Avenue and Terra Bella Avenue in Mountain View, then cautiously entered the intersection to turn left with turn signals on; just after it began to move, another vehicle struck it from behind.

location: Gemende Drive, Riverside, CA
description: While the Ohmio Lift autonomous shuttle was driving on Gemende Drive toward Airport Drive in Riverside, a Ford Flex minivan reversed from a perpendicular parking space on the right side of the road into the shuttle’s path and hit its side; the system detected the vehicle and commanded braking within milliseconds, brake pressure ramped rapidly, the reversing minivan continued until impact about 358 ms after first detection, and the shuttle came to a complete stop in roughly 1.18 seconds.

location: Trestle Glen Road, Oakland, CA
description: On March 29, 2025 in Oakland, a Pony.ai Lincoln MKZ being driven manually eastbound on Trestle Glen Road brushed the side mirror of a parked Toyota Avalon; there were no injuries or police response, and the safety operator later drove the vehicle to Pony.ai’s Fremont office after leaving contact details for the parked car’s owner.

location: 2701 Orchard Pkwy, San Jose, CA
description: On November 18, 2025, a Tensor autonomous Chrysler Pacifica being driven manually and stopped in traffic on Orchard Parkway in San Jose was struck when the truck in front began backing up and its rear rack hit the AV’s front blind‑spot sensor pod; the AV driver honked but had no room or time to reverse, and the AV only suffered light scratching.

location: N. Rengstorff Avenue near E. Charleston Road, Mountain View, CA

Charleston Road when a bus behind it tried to pass by crossing the double yellow centerline into the opposing lane; as the bus drew alongside, its passenger side struck the rear driver side of the stationary AV, and both vehicles sustained damage.

location: La Cienega Boulevard at W 83rd Street, Inglewood, CA
description: On March 27, 2025 in Inglewood, a Waymo Jaguar I-PACE with its Level 4 ADS engaged was stopped in southbound traffic at a red light on La Cienega Boulevard near W 83rd Street when a 2014 Honda Accord approached from behind and its front struck the rear of the stationary AV; only the passenger car’s damage is noted.

location: 170 N. Church Lane, Los Angeles, CA

location: Broadway at Euclid Court, Santa Monica, CA

location: Parking lot entrance of 785 Moscow Street, San Francisco, CA

location: S. Mansfield Avenue near Westhaven Street, Los Angeles, CA

Mansfield Avenue, where a pickup protruded into the roadway; after the AV stopped with hazards on and shifted to reverse to yield space to a northbound Kia Sportage Hybrid, the SUV continued forward and its left side struck the rear left side of the stationary AV as it tried to pass between the AV and the pickup.

location: Parking lot at 1980 W. Reservoir Street, Los Angeles, CA
description: On October 4, 2025 in a parking lot at 1980 W. location: Parking lot at 1980 W. Reservoir Street, Los Angeles, CA
description: On October 4, 2025 in a parking lot at 1980 W. location: Clinton Street near N. Kenmore Avenue, Los Angeles, CA
description: On October 9, 2025 in Los Angeles, a Waymo Jaguar I-Pace operating eastbound in Level 4 autonomous mode on a narrow, parked-up stretch of Clinton Street stopped to yield to a westbound Lexus 450h+; while passing, the SUV’s left side struck the rear-left of the stationary AV, leading to reported damage to the SUV.

location: Parking lot at 350 Pacific Avenue, San Francisco, CA

location: Ilona Avenue near Fox Hills Drive, Los Angeles, CA

location: Midcrest Way near Cityview Way, San Francisco, CA

location: Beverly Boulevard at N. Curson Avenue, Los Angeles, CA

location: Bundy Drive near W. Olympic Boulevard, Los Angeles, CA

location: W. 3rd Street at Witmer Street, Los Angeles, CA

location: Logue Avenue at E. Middlefield Road, Mountain View, CA

location: Main Street near W. 37th Place, Los Angeles, CA

The AV signaled and began a lane change left while a test driver took manual control 0.8 seconds before impact; during this maneuver the rebounding tire struck the AV's passenger side, causing minor damage while Level 4 ADS was not engaged.

location: Interstate 280 near Exit 22 (Junipero Serra Freeway), Portola Valley, CA
description: On May 1, 2025 near Exit 22 on Junipero Serra Freeway, a Waymo 2021 Jaguar I-Pace traveling northwest in the rightmost lane behind a pickup experienced a hazard when the pickup's rear passenger-side tire detached, hit the right barrier, and bounced back into the AV's lane. The AV signaled and began a lane change left while a test driver took manual control 0.8 seconds before impact; during this maneuver the rebounding tire struck the AV's passenger side, causing minor damage while Level 4 ADS was not engaged.

location: Broadway near Stockton Street, San Francisco, CA
description: On May 10, 2025 on Broadway near Stockton Street in San Francisco, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace traveling westbound in the rightmost lane slowed for a queue of traffic. A 2020 Ford Transit van approached from behind and its front end struck the rear of the slowing AV, causing minor rear-end damage while the Level 4 ADS was engaged and resulting in a reported minor injury to an AV passenger.

location: S. Van Ness Avenue at 21st Street, San Francisco, CA
description: On May 10, 2025 at about 4:18 AM on S. Van Ness Avenue at 21st Street in San Francisco, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace was stopped facing south in the rightmost lane at a red signal when a following passenger car approached from behind and its front made contact with the rear of the stationary AV, damaging both vehicles while the Level 4 ADS was engaged. The crash was reportable under NHTSA Standing General Order 2021-01 Request No. 1 because a vehicle was towed from the scene.

location: Venice Boulevard near Frances Avenue, Los Angeles, CA
description: On May 14, 2025 on Venice Boulevard near Frances Avenue in Los Angeles, a Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace traveling northeast in the right lane encountered a dog entering the roadway from the southeast sidewalk. The AV began braking and the test driver then took manual control and continued braking to a stop while the dog crossed in front. A 2010 Honda Civic LX following behind swerved left, its front passenger side struck the AV's rear driver side, and it continued into the left lane where it hit the dog and then stopped. The dog left the scene and both vehicles were damaged while the AV was in manual mode with Level 4 ADS disengaged.

location: Cypress Avenue near Clark Avenue, San Bruno, CA
description: On June 20, 2025 on Cypress Avenue near Clark Avenue in San Bruno, a driverless Waymo 2021 Jaguar I-Pace traveling northbound in autonomous mode contacted a fallen utility line hanging across the roadway with its front end, causing minor damage while the Level 4 ADS was engaged.

location: Florida Street near 22nd Street, San Francisco, CA
description: On June 21, 2025 on Florida Street near 22nd Street in San Francisco, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace traveling southbound on a narrow street stopped to yield to a northbound heavy truck. While the AV remained stopped, the 2024 Mercedes-Benz Sprinter 4500 heavy truck moved forward to pass and its driver side contacted the AV's rear driver side, damaging both vehicles while the Level 4 ADS was engaged.

location: Euclid Court near Broadway, Santa Monica, CA
description: On July 16, 2025 on Euclid Court near Broadway in Santa Monica, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace turned left from Broadway onto Euclid Court and then stopped behind a lane-stopped SUV. The 2008 Ford Escape SUV began reversing and its rear contacted the front of the stationary AV while the Level 4 ADS was engaged, causing minor damage to the AV.

location: 584 Brannan Street (parking lot), San Francisco, CA
description: On July 20, 2025 in a parking lot at 584 Brannan Street in San Francisco, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace was parked in a stall facing southeast with its Level 4 ADS engaged when a 2023 Porsche Cayenne Coupe SUV parked directly in front reversed and its rear contacted the AV's front, causing damage to the SUV.

location: S. Grevillea Avenue at E. Spruce Avenue, Inglewood, CA
description: On July 21, 2025 in Inglewood, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace traveling southbound on S. Grevillea Avenue slowed for a queue of traffic stopped at a stop sign at E. Spruce Avenue. A 2015 Kia Forte X traveling in the same direction approached from behind and its front contacted the rear of the AV, damaging both vehicles while the Level 4 ADS was engaged.

location: E. 15th Street at S. Alameda Street, Los Angeles, CA
description: On November 20, 2025 at E. 15th Street and S. Alameda Street in Los Angeles, a driverless Waymo 2024 Jaguar I-Pace was stopped at a red light with its right turn signal on, briefly initiated a right turn, then stopped again before entering S. Alameda Street. A 2019 Toyota C-HR SUV making a right turn behind proceeded forward and its front contacted the AV's rear, damaging both vehicles while the Level 4 ADS was engaged.

location: Toland Street near Galvez Avenue, San Francisco, CA
description: On June 12, 2025 on Toland Street near Galvez Avenue in San Francisco, a driverless Waymo 2021 Jaguar I-Pace traveling southwestbound passed a heavy truck parked on the right curb. A Toyota Tacoma pickup traveling southeastbound in an alley by 150 Toland Street then entered Toland Street ahead of the heavy truck into the AV's lane, and its front driver side struck the AV's front passenger side while the Level 4 ADS was engaged, damaging the AV.

location: First lane from right near 2772 San Tomas Expy, Santa Clara, CA
description: At about 45 mph on San Tomas Expressway near 2772, a driverless WeRide 2023 Nissan Leaf in the first lane from the right was traveling with little traffic ahead when a 2025 BMW X3 in the adjacent left lane made two abrupt right lane changes to reach an upcoming exit, merging into the Leaf's left front quarter panel. The impact forced the Leaf out of its lane onto a divide and then to a stop on the shoulder; both vehicles were moderately damaged, no injuries were found, and the Leaf required towing.

location: First lane from right near 2772 San Tomas Expy, Santa Clara, CA
description: At about 45 mph on San Tomas Expressway near 2772, a driverless WeRide 2023 Nissan Leaf in the first lane from the right was traveling with little traffic ahead when a 2025 BMW X3 in the adjacent left lane made two abrupt right lane changes to reach an upcoming exit and merged into the Leaf's left front quarter panel. The impact forced the Leaf out of its lane onto a divide and then to a stop on the shoulder; both vehicles were moderately damaged, no injuries were found, and the Leaf required towing.

location: First lane from right near 2772 San Tomas Expy, Santa Clara, CA
description: At about 45 mph on San Tomas Expressway near 2772, a driverless WeRide 2023 Nissan Leaf in the first lane from the right was traveling with little traffic ahead when a 2025 BMW X3 in the adjacent left lane made two abrupt right lane changes to reach an upcoming exit and merged into the Leaf's left front quarter panel. The impact forced the Leaf out of its lane onto a divide and then to a stop on the shoulder; both vehicles were moderately damaged, no injuries were found, and the Leaf required towing.

location: Alameda Street and Treat Avenue, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2017 Toyota Highlander test vehicle operating in manual mode was stopped in lane at a stop sign on eastbound Alameda Street, preparing to turn left onto Treat Avenue in San Francisco, when a 2015 Chevrolet Impala Limited making a wide right turn from Treat Avenue onto westbound Alameda Street struck the front of the stopped Zoox vehicle head-on. Both vehicles had moderate damage, police were not called, and the Zoox vehicle operator and the front-seat software operator reported injuries.

location: 16th Street towards Bryant Street, San Francisco, None
description: A Zoox 2017 Toyota Highlander test vehicle was westbound on 16th Street in the right-turn-only lane toward Bryant Street in autonomous mode, then the operator disengaged automation and manually stopped behind a bus. A few seconds later an e-bicyclist traveling westbound contacted the Zoox vehicle's rear bumper and left without exchanging information. Minor damage occurred and there were no reported injuries or police response.

location: 5th Street at Shipley Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2017 Toyota Highlander test vehicle in manual mode was traveling northwest on 5th Street, preparing to turn right onto Shipley Street in San Francisco, when it braked hard to yield to an e-bike in the bike lane starting to cross Shipley Street. A following motorcyclist then rear-ended the Zoox vehicle, causing minor rear-bumper damage. The motorcyclist refused to exchange information, no injuries were reported, and police were not called.

location: Brannan Street and 8th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: An unoccupied Zoox 2026 autonomous sedan was traveling northeast on Brannan Street through a green light at 8th Street in San Francisco when a southwest-bound Isuzu box truck attempted an unprotected left turn onto 8th Street across its path. The Zoox vehicle braked hard to yield, but the truck's left side mirror assembly contacted the Zoox vehicle's roof-mounted left rear sensor pod. The Zoox vehicle stopped, the truck completed its turn and pulled over, and the Zoox vehicle later cleared the intersection, pulled over, and returned to base with sensor damage and no reported injuries.

location: Harrison Street near 12th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: An unoccupied Zoox 2024 autonomous sedan in the right lane of northeast-bound Harrison Street near 12th Street in San Francisco gradually slowed to a stop when it encountered a passenger car ahead reversing to parallel park along the curb. The passenger car continued reversing and contacted the Zoox vehicle's right front fender, then left the scene without exchanging information. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage and police were notified.

location: Bay Street approaching Octavia Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2019 Toyota Highlander test vehicle, parallel-parked on eastbound Bay Street in San Francisco in manual mode, was sideswiped on the driver-side mirror by an eastbound BMW X5 in the adjacent lane. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage, the BMW driver left without exchanging information, no injuries were reported, and police were not called.

location: Bay Street approaching Octavia Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2019 Toyota Highlander test vehicle, parallel-parked on eastbound Bay Street in San Francisco in manual mode, was sideswiped on the driver-side mirror by an eastbound BMW X5 in the adjacent lane. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage, the BMW driver left without exchanging information, no injuries were reported, and police were not called.

location: 20th Street approaching Mission Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2017 Toyota Highlander test vehicle operating in manual mode was traveling east on 20th Street in stop-and-go traffic near the Mission Street traffic light when it inched forward and then slowed for stopped traffic ahead. A following Lexus RX SUV rear-ended the Zoox vehicle, causing minor rear-bumper damage. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: 16th Street at Potrero Avenue, San Francisco, CA
description: A 2024 Zoox sedan operating in autonomous mode was stopped for a red light on westbound 16th Street at Potrero Avenue in San Francisco when it was rear-ended by a following BMW X1 SUV that failed to stop. The SUV driver reversed and then departed without exchanging information. The Zoox vehicle later cleared the intersection, with minor damage to the license plate bracket and no reported injuries; police were not called. Video from the Zoox vehicle showed the SUV driver was not looking ahead prior to impact.

location: Howard Street towards 8th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox 2019 Toyota Highlander operating in autonomous mode in the left lane on southwest-bound Howard Street toward 8th Street encountered a ball and then a dog entering the roadway from between parked cars directly into its path. The vehicle braked but its underbody contacted the dog. The operator then disengaged autonomous mode, stopped, and reversed to free the dog. The owner reported no injuries at the scene, the dog and owner returned to the sidewalk, and the Zoox vehicle left. Police were not called. Zoox later received an email alleging abrasions and a possible cracked rib to the dog.

location: Bryant Street toward 19th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: An unoccupied 2026 Zoox sedan in autonomous mode was traveling north on Bryant Street toward 19th Street, slowing behind a nearly stopped 2025 Nissan Rogue SUV in the same lane. As the Zoox vehicle steered left to pass, the Rogue driver abruptly reversed without signaling to parallel park on the right side of the street. The Zoox vehicle braked to a near stop but was contacted on its right rear wheel as the Rogue swung into the parking space. The Zoox vehicle was later towed for inspection and found to have no damage, while the Rogue's left front bumper had minor apparent damage. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: Division Street at 9th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: An unoccupied 2026 Zoox sedan operating in autonomous mode was stopped at a green light on eastbound Division Street, waiting for traffic ahead to clear before turning left onto 9th Street. A Ford F-250 pickup was stopped directly behind it for the same light. After the light turned yellow, the pickup driver passed the stopped Zoox vehicle on the left, struck its left rear fender, and continued through the now-red light without stopping to exchange information. The Zoox vehicle then turned left to clear the intersection, stopped and pulled over, and was towed for inspection, which found minor damage. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: Michigan Avenue at Euclid Court, Santa Monica, CA
description: A 2019 Toyota Highlander Zoox test vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling southwest on Michigan Avenue toward Euclid Court in Santa Monica when a 2014 Volkswagen Tiguan SUV entered from Euclid Court traveling southeast, failed to yield the right-of-way, and moved into its path, striking the Zoox vehicle on the passenger side. The Zoox vehicle braked, the operator disengaged autonomy, continued braking, and steered left, but a collision could not be avoided. The Zoox vehicle sustained moderate damage and the Tiguan also sustained damage. No injuries were reported and police were not notified.

location: Bryant Street and 18th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A 2019 Toyota Highlander Zoox autonomous vehicle was stopped at a stop sign on southbound Bryant Street at 18th Street. As it began to move forward, it was rear-ended by a 2006 Nissan Pathfinder SUV that failed to stop. The Zoox vehicle showed no reported damage, but the safety operator later reported neck and lower back injuries. Camera footage indicated the Pathfinder driver was not looking ahead before or at the time of impact, and police were not called.

location: Laguna Street between Ellis St and Cleary Ct, San Francisco, CA
description: A 2017 Toyota Highlander Zoox test vehicle in manual mode was parallel parked along the right curb on southbound Laguna Street between Ellis Street and Cleary Court in San Francisco. A rider traveling south on a Lime e-scooter along the right curb appeared to let go of the scooter, after which the now-unoccupied scooter rolled into and struck the rear right side of the Zoox vehicle, causing minor damage. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: 17th Street and Valencia Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox autonomous vehicle was traveling eastbound on 17th Street, slowing to make an unprotected left turn onto Valencia Street in San Francisco when an oncoming left-turning vehicle accelerated abruptly. The Zoox vehicle braked in response and was rear-ended by a following Honda Fit. After the impact, the Zoox operator disengaged autonomy, continued through the intersection on 17th Street, and then pulled over to exchange information. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor rear-end damage, the Honda Fit had moderate front-left and hood damage, both the Zoox driver and front-seat software operator reported injuries, and police were not called.

location: 14th Street near Dolores Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox autonomous vehicle traveling eastbound in the left lane on 14th Street near Dolores Street slowed for a nearly stopped Tesla Model 3 ahead in the same lane. The Tesla then began reversing without signaling, apparently to enter a curb-lane parking space, while the Zoox vehicle braked to a stop and its operator disengaged autonomy. Vehicle 2 continued reversing while steering left, and its right-rear corner sideswiped the left-front corner of the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle reported no damage, Vehicle 2 had minor damage, no injuries occurred, and law enforcement was not notified.

location: 14th Street approaching Folsom St, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox test vehicle in manual mode was traveling westbound on 14th Street toward Folsom Street in San Francisco when it went around a double-parked vehicle in its lane and began re-entering the lane. At that moment, a parallel-parked 2009 Toyota Yaris pulled out ahead into the Zoox vehicle's travel path, and the Zoox vehicle's front passenger-side bumper contacted the Yaris driver's-side fender. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: Florida Street approaching Treat Avenue, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox test vehicle in manual mode, traveling north on Florida Street approaching Treat Avenue in San Francisco, slowed to a stop to allow an oncoming tow truck to pass. While passing, the tow truck's driver's-side mirror contacted the rear driver-side roof-mounted sensor pod on the Zoox vehicle, causing moderate damage to the pod. The tow-truck operator left without exchanging information; no injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: 11th Street towards Folsom Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox autonomous vehicle was traveling northeast on 11th Street approaching Folsom Street in San Francisco while a Volvo S60 was parallel parked on the right side in the same direction. The Volvo pulled out of its parking space, made a U-turn into the opposite travel lane, then crossed the double-yellow centerline and veered into the Zoox vehicle's lane. The Zoox vehicle braked for the encroaching car, but the Volvo still struck the driver's-side fender and both doors. The Zoox operator then disengaged autonomy and brought the vehicle to a stop. The Zoox vehicle sustained major side damage and was towed; the Volvo's frontal airbags deployed and it had moderate front driver's-side damage. The Volvo driver fled without exchanging information, police responded, and no injuries were reported.

location: Folsom Street at 6th Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox test vehicle in manual mode was traveling northeast on Folsom Street preparing to turn left onto 6th Street in San Francisco when a Volkswagen passenger car traveling southeast on 6th Street ran a red light, entered the intersection, and its front driver's side struck the Zoox vehicle's driver-side rear wheel area. The Volkswagen's front end was damaged and the driver left without exchanging information. The Zoox vehicle had moderate damage to the rear wheel and suspension and was towed. Police responded and no injuries were reported.

location: Treat Avenue near Bryant Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox autonomous sedan was double-parked southwest-bound on Treat Avenue near Bryant Street in San Francisco with brake and hazard lights activated while waiting for the next ride when a Chevrolet Volt that had been parallel parked in the adjacent right curb lane pulled out and attempted a multi-point U-turn ahead of it. During the maneuver, the Volt's driver's-side rear door contacted the Zoox vehicle's front left fender, causing minor fender damage. The Volt's driver stopped briefly to inspect both vehicles and then left without exchanging information. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: Frederick Street and Buena Vista Avenue, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox test vehicle operating in manual mode was traveling eastbound on Frederick Street and turning right onto Buena Vista Avenue in San Francisco when its front driver's-side wheel struck a traffic island to the left of the vehicle, damaging the wheel rim. No injuries were reported and police were not called.

location: Harrison Street near Columbia Square Street, San Francisco, CA
description: A Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling southwest in lane 4 on Harrison Street near Columbia Square in San Francisco while a Chevrolet Camaro ahead in lane 5 was attempting to pass a cyclist on the right. After the Zoox operator disengaged, the Camaro swerved left into lane 4 across the Zoox vehicle's path, and its driver-side quarter panel contacted the Zoox vehicle's passenger-side fender and front door. Both vehicles moved a short distance and pulled over to exchange information. Vehicle 2 appeared to have minor damage while the Zoox vehicle had no reported damage, no injuries occurred, and police were not called.

summary: Unoccupied Zoox autonomous vehicle stopped at a red light. After the light turned green, it proceeded straight through the intersection. A cyclist on an eBike, who had started moving before the signal changed, abruptly veered left into the AV's path in violation of a red crosswalk signal and the AV's right-of-way. The AV initiated hard braking but contact was unavoidable. The eBike struck the right front fender and body side, and the cyclist impacted the right front body. The cyclist left the scene on the eBike with no reported or apparent injuries. The AV sustained minor damage and was towed for inspection.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: An unoccupied Zoox vehicle in autonomous mode was traveling south on Bryant Street, slowing and preparing to make a right turn onto Division Street in San Francisco. At that time, an approaching e-scooterist was also traveling south on Bryant Street in the curb lane offset from the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle braked to a stop as the e-scooterist was beginning to enter the intersection. The e-scooterist then made contact with the right rear side of the stopped Zoox vehicle, and the e-scooterist fell to the ground next to the Zoox vehicle. The Zoox vehicle then started to move and completed the right turn onto Treat Avenue, coming to a stop a short distance down Treat Avenue. The e-scooterist then walked themself and the e-scooter over to the sidewalk, where they were met by a member of the Zoox operations team, and they reported a chipped tooth and jaw pain. The e-scooterist declined medical attention and rode their e-scooter from the scene after exchanging information. There was no damage to the Zoox vehicle and the police were not called.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in autonomous mode, was heading east on Alameda Street toward Harrison Street in San Francisco. It then encountered a van hauling a trailer (Vehicle 2) traveling west, partially occupying both the westbound and eastbound lanes on Alameda Street. The Zoox vehicle slowed for the oncoming Vehicle 2; then its operator disengaged from autonomy and manually brought the vehicle to a complete stop. As Vehicle 2 passed, the driver's side of Vehicle 2 scraped the driver's side of the stopped Zoox vehicle. The driver of Vehicle 2 failed to stop and exchange information. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage, and no injuries were reported. Camera footage from the Zoox vehicle shows that the operator of Vehicle 2 steered toward it without appearing to attempt to avoid making contact. The police were later notified about the incident.

After the light turned green, and before the Zoox vehicle started to move, it was rear ended by a passenger car (Vehicle 2) that was traveling directly behind. The Zoox vehicle operator then disengaged from autonomy, completed the left turn, and pulled over on Howard Street to exchange information. The Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage to the rear bumper. There were no reported injuries, and police were not called. The Zoox vehicle camera footage shows that the Vehicle 2 driver was not looking ahead at the roadway before or at the time of contact.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in autonomous mode and traveling northeast on Bryant Street, was preparing to make a right on red traffic light on 10th Street in San Francisco. After fully stopping at the stop line, it advanced into the crosswalk before yielding to cross traffic with the right of way. A bicyclist, riding northwest on the sidewalk along 10th Street, then approached the crosswalk. As the bicyclist entered the crosswalk, the operator of the Zoox vehicle disengaged from autonomy and began to manually drive the vehicle forward. The bicyclist veered right towards the front of the Zoox vehicle and made contact with the front passenger side door of the Zoox vehicle. The bicycle then fell to the ground next to the Zoox vehicle. After stopping for a brief conversation with the bicyclist, the Zoox vehicle operator proceeded to make the right turn onto 10th Street, inadvertently driving over the front wheel of the fallen bicycle. The operator completed the turn and pulled over to check for damages and exchange information. The Zoox vehicle did not sustain any damage; however, the front wheel rim of the bicycle was damaged. There were no reported injuries, and the police were not notified.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) operating in autonomous mode turned right onto Laguna Street from eastbound Hermann Street, approaching the intersection with Market Street in San Francisco. As it was entering the intersection, the Zoox vehicle briefly braked to a stop, and just as it started to move, it was rear ended by a passenger car (Vehicle 2) traveling directly behind. The Zoox vehicle operator then disengaged from autonomy, cleared the intersection, and pulled over to exchange information. The rear bumper of the Zoox vehicle sustained minor damage, and its software operator, who was seated in the front passenger seat, reported "soreness in [the] right shoulder" after the collision. The police were not called.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1) was operating in autonomous mode, traveling east in the right lane of 15th Street between Mission and Wiese Streets in San Francisco. As it approached a double-parked passenger car (Vehicle 2) in the lane, the operator of the Zoox vehicle disengaged from autonomous driving. The operator then moved into the left lane and maneuvered around Vehicle 2. The driver of Vehicle 2 started moving just as the Zoox vehicle was re-entering the right lane, and shortly after, the right front area of the Zoox vehicle made contact with the left front area of Vehicle 2. The Zoox vehicle did not sustain any damage, but Vehicle 2 sustained moderate damage to its left front door. There were no reported injuries, and the police were not called.

section_5_accident_details_description.narrative: A Zoox vehicle (Vehicle 1), operating in manual mode, was heading south on Alabama Street, in the southbound lane, approaching Mariposa Street in San Francisco, when it encountered a passenger car (Vehicle 2) traveling north and occupying both the northbound and southbound lanes on Alabama Street. The Zoox vehicle slowed and moved to the right for the oncoming Vehicle 2; however, as Vehicle 2 passed, its driver's side mirror made contact with the driver's side rear of the Zoox vehicle. The driver of Vehicle 2 failed to stop and exchange information. The Zoox vehicle did not sustain any damage, but Vehicle 2 appeared to have sustained minor damage to its driver's side mirror. There were no reported injuries, and the police were not notified.
